Comments:       Minimum System Requirements
			-Pentium III CPU
			-256MB RAM + Swap

		Total number of dependencies =~ 200

		Installation
		-------------
		Step 1-) Set root and <user> password
			 $ sudo passwd root
			 $ sudo passwd <user>

		Step 2-) Setup environment
			 $ gnome-desktop-base-setup

		Step 3-) Backup and reboot
			 $ filetool.sh backup
			 $ sudo reboot
		
		Optional GNOME packages:
			-file-roller (archive manager, nautilus plugin)
			-brasero (cd/dvd burning application)
			-totem (movie player & thumbnailer)
			-gnote (tomboy notes, sticky notes panel plugin)
			-gnome-games, gbrainy, gnome-hearts (small games)
			-epiphany (web browser)
			-evince (ps/pdf/djvulibre/tiff document viewer, and a thumbnailer for the supported file types)
			-gnome-colors & arc-colors & shiki-colors (icons/backgrounds/themes)
			-rhythmbox (music player)
			-evolution, balsa (e-mail clients)
			-gnome-backgrounds (set of background images)
			-cheese (web cam application)
			-eog-plugins (flickr uploader integrated with nautilus)
			-banshee (music management and player application)
			-vinagre & vino (remote desktop server and client)
			-gcalctool (calculator)
			-gconf-editor (graphical editor for the GConf configuration system)
			-gnome-audio (desktop sounds)
			-gnome-bluetooth (bluetooth connection wizard)
			-nautilus-sendto (through nautilus context menu, send files to usb, bluetooth devices or anyone via mail)
			-xscreensaver-base or xscreensaver-extra for more screensavers to use with gnome-screensaver
			-network-manager-gnome (NetworkManager GNOME client)

		Other optional packages: acpid, cpufreqd, wicd, samba3, avahi ...

		PULSEAUDIO is the only option and will be installed for sound.

		This extension requires Xorg.
		This extension is PPI compatible.

